jQuery Responsive Full Width Slider
-----------------------------------

What it is supposed to do, when it's done:

Slide through multiple DIVs. The triggers for the slides are part of the slides itself.


The HTML looks like:

<div class="slideContainer">

  <div class="slide" name="0">
    CONTENT
    <a name="1" class="slideMover"> Go to Slide 1 </a>
    <a name="2" class="slideMover"> Go to Slide 2 </a>
  </div>

  <div class="slide" name="1">
    CONTENT
    <a name="0" class="slideMover"> Go to Slide 0 </a>
    <a name="2" class="slideMover"> Go to Slide 2 </a>
  </div>

  <div class="slide" name="2">
    CONTENT
    <a name="0" class="slideMover"> Go to Slide 0 </a>
    <a name="1" class="slideMover"> Go to Slide 1 </a>
  </div>

</div>


The slides automatically scale with the browser-width.




